description.p:
(a) treating an optically pure 2R, 3S or 2S, 3R diol of formula (III) with an agent capable of introducing a sulfoxide, or carbonyl group, in the presence of a base and an organic solvent, at a temperature in the range of -78 (degree)  C. to 100 (degree)  C.;


(b) resting the resultant mixture for a period of 1 to 15 hours;


(c) pouring the rested mixture into water; and


(d) extracting the aqueous mixture with an organic solvent to obtain the compound of formula (IV).
